First find the total distance to the beach: 16 blocks * 1/8 mile/block = <<16*1/8=128/1>>128/1 miles
Then find how long in hours Jack has to get to the beach: 10 minutes / 60 minutes/hour = 10/60 hour
Then divide the distance Jack needs to cover by the time in hours he has to find how fast he needs to jog: 128/1 miles / 10/60 hour = 768 miles/hour
#### 768
